<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="457" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1776,2019]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="457" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1776,1802]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has a single stem with filaments in rows which is common in the genus and the 
<specimenCount pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of anisochela and sigmancistras of microsclere spicules are also typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1901" box="[1046,1203,1812,1838]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1203,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Asbestopluma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="indiyansis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1265,1289,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1304,1328,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">indiyansis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[188,279,1848,1875]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[188,272,1848,1874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
species that most closely matches the habit and spicule complement and spicule morphology of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hestetun, Rapp &amp; Xavier, 2017" authorityName="Hestetun, Rapp &amp; Xavier" authorityYear="2017" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pseudoisochela" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1362,1387,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1403,1427,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,324,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">pseudoisochela</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hestetun, J. T. &amp; Rapp, H. T. &amp; Xavier, J." box="[331,691,1884,1911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="166 - 189" refId="ref17430" refString="Hestetun, J. T., Rapp, H. T. &amp; Xavier, J. (2017 a) Carnivorous sponges (Porifera, Cladorhizidae) from the Southwest Indian Ocean Ridge seamounts. Deep Sea Research Part II: Topical Studies in Oceanography, 137, 166 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. dsr 2.2016.03.004" type="journal article" year="2017">Hestetun, Rapp &amp; Xavier, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt, 1875)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[702,1087,1884,1911]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pennatula" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[702,727,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[743,768,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[784,896,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">pennatula</emphasis>
(Schmidt, 1875)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Topsent, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Topsent" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="belgicae" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1142,1167,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1184,1208,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) cf. 
<emphasis box="[1261,1356,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">belgicae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref19045" refString="Topsent, E. (1901) Notice preliminaire sur les eponges recueillies par l'Expedition Antarctique Belge. Archives de Zoologie Experimentaleet Generale, Series 3, 9 (Notes et Revue), V - XVI" type="book" year="1901">Topsent, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[278,473,1920,1946]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="indiyansis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[278,303,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[319,343,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[359,473,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">indiyansis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[480,570,1920,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[480,564,1920,1946]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from other known species by having 
<specimenCount box="[1071,1179,1921,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of anisochelae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1610]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[160,1427,181,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Asbestopluma (Asbestopluma) indiyansis sp. nov. A. Mycalostyle. B. Subtylostyle. C. Desmas. D–E. Anisochela I front and back view. F–H. Anisochela II front and back view. I–K. Anisochela III, L–N. Sigmancistras including an immature stage (K)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figure 3C–E</figureCitation>
). The new species appears similar morphology to that of the distal parts of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hestetun, Rapp &amp; Xavier" authorityYear="2017" box="[1076,1332,1956,1982]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pseudoisochela" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1076,1100,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1117,1142,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1159,1332,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">pseudoisochela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the SWIOR but differs in having the desmas branching forms. The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Topsent" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1220,1436,1992,2018]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="belgicae" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1220,1244,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1262,1286,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A.</emphasis>
) cf. 
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">belgicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Southern Ocean and Southeastern Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun, V. M." box="[734,878,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 372" refId="ref17792" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. 1 Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E., Andriyashev, A. &amp; Ushakov, P. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958). Academy of Sciences of the U. S. S. R., Israel Program for Scientific Translations Ltd., Jerusalem, pp. 1 - 372, pls. I - VIII. [English translation]" type="book chapter" year="1964">Koltun 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." box="[887,1041,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref19045" refString="Topsent, E. (1901) Notice preliminaire sur les eponges recueillies par l'Expedition Antarctique Belge. Archives de Zoologie Experimentaleet Generale, Series 3, 9 (Notes et Revue), V - XVI" type="book" year="1901">Topsent 1901</bibRefCitation>
). This new species is unique among the known 
<taxonomicName box="[277,522,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis box="[277,434,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Asbestopluma</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by a combination of its morphology and the unique shape of its anisochelae, and they are roughly spherical. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bravo &amp; Hajdu, 2011" authorityName="Bravo &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2011" box="[458,1035,223,249]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="bitrichela" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[458,615,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Asbestopluma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[632,657,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[673,782,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">bitrichela</emphasis>
Bravo &amp; Hajdu, 2011
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kelly &amp; Vacelet, 2011" authorityName="Kelly &amp; Vaceleet" authorityYear="2011" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="desmophora" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[1047,1071,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1087,1112,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1128,1266,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">desmophora</emphasis>
Kelly &amp; Vacelet, 2011
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes &amp; Hajdu, 2014" authorityName="Lopes &amp; Hajdu" authorityYear="2014" box="[264,731,259,285]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="inexpectata" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[264,288,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[305,329,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[346,475,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">inexpectata</emphasis>
Lopes &amp; Hajdu, 2014
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole, 2022" authorityName="Rengaiyan &amp; Ingole" authorityYear="2022" box="[743,939,259,285]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="indiyansis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[743,767,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[784,809,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[825,939,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">indiyansis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[947,1039,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[947,1032,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Topsent, 1929)" baseAuthorityName="Topsent" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="stylivarians" subGenus="Helophloeina">
<emphasis box="[1095,1112,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1136,1288,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Helophloeina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1306,1437,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">stylivarians</emphasis>
(Topsent, 1929)
</taxonomicName>
have an unusual desmas and all branching forms. This new species can be distinguished from these species most easily by different spicule morphology and sizes for the smaller megascleres and microsclere.
</paragraph>
